Day 26:
Step 0:


________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


1. Create an Azure DataBricks:
Step 1: You can search DataBricks in the search bar.
Step 2: Click on to create for creating an Azure DataBrick.
Step 3: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Resource Group name
        b. Subscription
        c. DataBrick name
        d. Region
        e. Pricing tier - free trial
Step 4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource to view your Azure DataBrick.


_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

2. Creating an Storage Account:
Step 1: You can search STORAGE ACCOUNTS in Search bar.
Step 2: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Storage Accounts name
        b. Performance - Standard
        c. Region
        d. Performance
        e. Access Tier - hot
Step 3: Then click on CREATE when you go to review+create.
Step 4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource group to view your Storage Account.

________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

3. Launching Azure DataBrick:
Step 1: In Overview, click on Launch Databrick.
Step 2: Enter your Microsoft mail for login in and enter the password.
Step 3: It will take you to the Home page of the Databrick.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

4. Create a new CLuster in Az DataBricks:
Step 1: In the menu click on create new cluster.
Step 2: Enter the necessary details:
      a. Cluster Mode
      b. Cluster Name
      c. Pool
      d. DataBricks in Runtime version
      e. Python version
      f. Worker type
      g. Driver type
Step 3: Click on compute to create your Cluster.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

5. Creating Scripts in Az DataBricks:
Step 1: Open a Noyebook in the Workspace which is located in the menu bar.
Step 2: Select the Language you want to code with and enter the code.
Step 3: For run, click on Shift + Enter key.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

6. Uploading file:
STep 1: Open the conatiner and upload the JSON file in the STorage Account you created.
Step 2: Go to the DataBrick and Script in scala.
Step 3: Write the code...

